Transmissible spongiform encephalopathies, or prion diseases, are mammalian neurodegenerative diseases leading to rapidly progressive neurological dysfunction (1). They include sheep scrapie, bovine spongiform encephalopathies, and Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease in humans (1-3). In these disorders, the host cellular prion protein (PrPC)1 is converted to an abnormal conformer
